Both parasites are maintained in a variety of transmission cycles that can operate independently, but what is not understood are the circumstances under which such cycles may interact and result in zoonotic transfer (Fig. 1
). In this respect, establishing a correct taxonomy for both parasites has provided the basis for better understanding the links between infections in domestic animals and humans (Table 1
). It is only recently with the advent of molecular typing tools that both the taxonomy and epidemiology of infections with Giardia and Cryptosporidium are now being resolved.
